<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Physical Therapy and Rehabilitation</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">FZT 270</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Summer Clinical Practice</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Make patient observation Under the supervision of a physical therapist, and , apply basic measurement and evaluation methods by communicating with the patient, electrotherapy and light modalities, basic exercise applications (EHA, stretching, resistance exercise training, massage, dynamic lumbar stabilization, relaxation exercises, balance and proprioception developer exercises, aerobic exercises and practices to follow, exercise prescription, planning, implementation, and if necessary modify applications.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Reading the lecture notes of Physical modalities and Electrotherapy, Manual therapy, Therapeutic exercises, Measurement and evaluation in physiotherapy, Kinesiology biomechanics</Data></Cell>
